# OBS is stowed as one folded directory symlink (~/.config/obs-studio points at
# this dir), so OBS writes its entire runtime state straight into the repo and
# dirties the tree on every launch: window geometry, dock layout, version
# markers, auto-downloaded RTMP service lists (~70KB), logs, crash dumps, scene
# .bak backups, and the websocket server password.
#
# So we whitelist: ignore everything, then re-include only the two files that
# define the actual setup. If you add a new scene collection or profile and want
# it tracked, add it explicitly below.

/*
!/.gitignore

# descend into basic/, ignore its contents by default
!/basic/
/basic/*

# scene collection: scenes, sources, mixer
!/basic/scenes/
/basic/scenes/*
!/basic/scenes/Untitled.json

# profile: encoder, output, video, audio, hotkeys
!/basic/profiles/
/basic/profiles/*
!/basic/profiles/Untitled/
/basic/profiles/Untitled/*
!/basic/profiles/Untitled/basic.ini
